+## WALLET-210 Service Partner Pilot Rehearsal
+
+Run this rehearsal in staging with synthetic data before any partner pilot
+session. The environment must already have the WALLET-170 public API blackbox,
+WALLET-180 proof verifier, WALLET-190 retention/deletion, and WALLET-200
+analytics governance evidence archived for the same deployment.
+
+Required setup:
+
+- `WALLET_API_ORIGIN` points to the staging wallet API.
+- `WALLET_UI_ORIGIN` points to the matching 211-AI UI.
+- `WALLET_ID`, `WALLET_OWNER_DID`, `WALLET_OWNER_KEY_HEX`,
+  `PILOT_PARTNER_DID`, `PILOT_PARTNER_KEY_HEX`, and
+  `PILOT_ANALYST_DID` are synthetic pilot values.
+- `WALLET_SERVICES_JSONL` is loaded with the staging 211 service directory.
+- The analytics template has WALLET-200 approval evidence and only allows
+  derived fields such as `county` and `need_category`.
+
+Pilot sequence:
+
+1. Add one document and one location.
+
+   ```bash
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"actor_did\":\"${WALLET_OWNER_DID}\",\"key_hex\":\"${WALLET_OWNER_KEY_HEX}\",\"filename\":\"pilot-intake.txt\",\"text\":\"Synthetic rent and SNAP support note\"}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/documents/text"
+
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"actor_did\":\"${WALLET_OWNER_DID}\",\"lat\":45.515232,\"lon\":-122.678385}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/locations"
+   ```
+
+   Open
+   `${WALLET_UI_ORIGIN}/?walletApiBaseUrl=${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}&walletId=${WALLET_ID}&actorDid=${WALLET_OWNER_DID}#/uploads`
+   and confirm the upload is listed with storage status and no plaintext
+   contact details or coordinates.
+
+2. Share purpose-bound access with the partner.
+
+   ```bash
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"record_id\":\"${DOCUMENT_RECORD_ID}\",\"requester_did\":\"${PILOT_PARTNER_DID}\",\"ability\":\"record/analyze\",\"purpose\":\"benefits_navigation\"}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/access-requests"
+   ```
+
+   Open `#/recipient-access` as the owner, confirm the helper, approve the
+   request, and record the active grant receipt. The receipt must show the
+   partner DID, `record/analyze`, `benefits_navigation`, and `status=active`.
+
+3. Verify partner use is bounded.
+
+   Open `#/recipient-access` as `PILOT_PARTNER_DID` with
+   `audienceKeyHex=${PILOT_PARTNER_KEY_HEX}` and run redacted analysis. The
+   result may show derived need categories and an encrypted artifact reference;
+   it must not show names, emails, phone numbers, SSNs, or document text.
+
+4. Match services from coarse location only.
+
+   ```bash
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"issuer_did\":\"${WALLET_OWNER_DID}\",\"issuer_key_hex\":\"${WALLET_OWNER_KEY_HEX}\",\"audience_did\":\"${PILOT_PARTNER_DID}\",\"audience_key_hex\":\"${PILOT_PARTNER_KEY_HEX}\"}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/locations/${LOCATION_RECORD_ID}/coarse-grants"
+
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"grant_id\":\"${COARSE_GRANT_ID}\",\"actor_did\":\"${PILOT_PARTNER_DID}\",\"actor_key_hex\":\"${PILOT_PARTNER_KEY_HEX}\",\"purpose\":\"service_matching\"}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/locations/${LOCATION_RECORD_ID}/coarse-invocations"
+
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"location_record_id\":\"${LOCATION_RECORD_ID}\",\"actor_did\":\"${PILOT_PARTNER_DID}\",\"actor_key_hex\":\"${PILOT_PARTNER_KEY_HEX}\",\"invocation_token\":\"${COARSE_INVOCATION_TOKEN}\",\"need_terms\":[\"housing\"],\"limit\":5}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/services/match"
+   ```
+
+   Pass criteria: service reasons reference need terms and coarse location
+   eligibility only; exact latitude/longitude values are absent from output and
+   logs.
+
+5. Prove service-area eligibility without precise coordinates.
+
+   ```bash
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"issuer_did\":\"${WALLET_OWNER_DID}\",\"audience_did\":\"${PILOT_PARTNER_DID}\"}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/locations/${LOCATION_RECORD_ID}/region-proof-grants"
+   ```
+
+   Open `#/proof-center` as the partner, enter `LOCATION_RECORD_ID`,
+   `REGION_GRANT_ID`, and `multnomah_county`, then create the proof. Archive
+   the proof receipt from `GET /wallets/${WALLET_ID}/proofs`. Public inputs
+   must include claim, region ID, and region policy hash only.
+
+6. Contribute to approved aggregate analytics.
+
+   ```bash
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"actor_did\":\"${WALLET_OWNER_DID}\",\"template_id\":\"${PILOT_TEMPLATE_ID}\"}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/analytics/consents/from-template"
+
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"actor_did\":\"${WALLET_OWNER_DID}\",\"consent_id\":\"${CONSENT_ID}\",\"template_id\":\"${PILOT_TEMPLATE_ID}\",\"fields\":{\"county\":\"Multnomah\",\"need_category\":\"housing\"}}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/analytics/contributions"
+
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"actor_did\":\"${PILOT_ANALYST_DID}\",\"epsilon\":0.25,\"min_cohort_size\":2}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/analytics/${PILOT_TEMPLATE_ID}/count"
+   ```
+
+   Pass criteria: the aggregate is released only when the approved cohort
+   threshold is met, raw counts remain suppressed when policy requires noisy
+   counts, and the privacy-budget spend is recorded.
+
+7. Revoke and prove revocation.
+
+   Revoke from `#/recipient-access` as the owner or call:
+
+   ```bash
+   curl -fsS -X POST -H "content-type: application/json" \
+     -d "{\"actor_did\":\"${WALLET_OWNER_DID}\",\"reason\":\"pilot complete\"}" \
+     "${WALLET_API_ORIGIN}/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/access-requests/${ACCESS_REQUEST_ID}/revoke"
+   ```
+
+   Re-run the partner analysis invocation and service-matching invocation. Both
+   must fail with a revoked or inactive grant error. If analytics participation
+   is ending, also revoke the analytics consent and confirm future
+   contributions for that consent are rejected.
+
+8. Audit the full workflow.
+
+   Open `#/audit` as the owner and archive `GET /wallets/${WALLET_ID}/audit`.
+   Required actions include `record/add`, `access/request`, `access/approve`,
+   `invocation/issue`, `invocation/verify`, `record/analyze_redacted`,
+   `location/read_coarse`, `proof/create`, `analytics/consent_create`,
+   `analytics/contribute`, `analytics/query`, and `access/revoke`. Evidence
+   must contain record IDs, grant IDs, proof IDs, template IDs, and status
+   metadata only.
+
+Local automation equivalent:
+
+```bash
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui test -- tests/fullstack-wallet.spec.ts
+```
+
+The fullstack spec includes the WALLET-210 browser/API pilot path and should be
+archived with the staging pilot readiness packet.
+
