+## 211 Service Partner Pilot Reference
+
+Use this flow for a WALLET-210 staging pilot only after the WALLET-170
+third-party blackbox harness, WALLET-180 verifier cutover packet, WALLET-190
+retention dry run, and WALLET-200 analytics governance review have passing or
+archived evidence for the same staging environment.
+
+Pilot actors:
+
+| Actor | DID role | Allowed purpose |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| Wallet owner | `owner_did` / active controller | Add records, approve and revoke grants, review audit. |
+| 211 service partner | `audience_did` / requester | Use purpose-bound document analysis, coarse location matching, and proof creation only. |
+| Analytics reviewer | service DID or reviewer DID | Run approved aggregate templates after consent and contribution. |
+
+Required UI/API surfaces:
+
+| Pilot step | UI surface | API surface | Privacy evidence |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| Add documents | `#/uploads` | `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/documents` or `/documents/text` | Record list shows descriptors and storage status, not plaintext. |
+| Add location | staging setup/API | `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/locations` | Precise coordinates remain encrypted. |
+| Share partner access | `#/recipient-access` | `/access-requests`, `/access-requests/{request_id}/approve`, `/grant-receipts` | Grant receipt records purpose, resource, ability, and status. |
+| Service matching | partner workflow/API | `/locations/{record_id}/coarse-grants`, `/coarse-invocations`, `/services/match` | Match output contains service reasons and no precise coordinates. |
+| Eligibility proof | `#/proof-center` | `/locations/{record_id}/region-proof-grants`, `/region-proofs`, `/proofs` | Public inputs include claim, region ID, and policy hash only. |
+| Aggregate analytics | `#/analytics` and reviewer API | `/analytics/templates`, `/analytics/consents/from-template`, `/analytics/contributions`, `/analytics/{template_id}/count` | Template is approved; contribution uses derived fields; release obeys k-threshold and budget. |
+| Revoke partner access | `#/recipient-access` | `/access-requests/{request_id}/revoke` or `/grants/{grant_id}/revoke` | Revoked grants block later invocation, decrypt, analyze, proof, match, or export attempts. |
+| Audit workflow | `#/audit` | `GET /wallets/{wallet_id}/audit` | Timeline contains record add, access, invocation, proof, analytics, revocation, and query events. |
+
+Pilot pass criteria:
+
+- The partner can complete only the approved purpose-bound action. A mismatched
+  purpose, revoked grant, expired grant, wrong actor DID, or disallowed output
+  type fails closed.
+- Browser views for uploads, proof center, analytics, recipient access, and
+  audit do not render plaintext documents, emails, phone numbers, SSNs, precise
+  coordinates, proof witnesses, key material, bearer tokens, or verifier
+  credentials.
+- Location eligibility is demonstrated with `location_region` proof receipts.
+  `location_distance` remains outside the visible Proof Center until the
+  distance verifier evidence is separately approved.
+- Aggregate analytics is released only through approved template IDs with
+  consent, nullifier, k-threshold, privacy-budget, retention, and reviewer
+  evidence from WALLET-200.
+- Archive the UI test run, API audit timeline, proof receipts, aggregate result
+  summary, revoked receipt list, and blocked post-revocation call as the pilot
+  readiness artifact.
+
